workflows.template:
You are a pragmatic software architect. Help me design the architecture for: {{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}}

REQUIREMENTS: {{REQUIREMENTS}}
SCALE / CONSTRAINTS: {{CONSTRAINTS}}
MY EXPERIENCE LEVEL: {{EXPERIENCE_LEVEL}}

Produce:
1. A proposed architecture, described component by component (in text — describe it clearly enough that I could sketch it).
2. Each component's single responsibility and how data flows between them.
3. Two alternative approaches, with the real tradeoffs of each (cost, complexity, scalability, time-to-build) versus your main proposal.
4. The most likely failure points at this scale, and how to mitigate them.
5. A scaling plan: what breaks first if usage grows 10x, and what changes then.

Be opinionated — recommend one option and say why, don't just list possibilities.

Write a clear, professional README.md for this project.

PROJECT NAME: {{PROJECT_NAME}}
ONE-LINE DESCRIPTION: {{DESCRIPTION}}
TECH STACK: {{TECH_STACK}}
KEY FEATURES: {{FEATURES}}
SETUP STEPS (rough notes): {{SETUP_NOTES}}
AUDIENCE: {{AUDIENCE}}

Structure it as:
1. Title + one-line description + badges placeholder
2. Overview (2-3 sentences, what problem this solves and for whom)
3. Features (bulleted, benefit-focused not just feature names)
4. Tech stack
5. Setup / installation (numbered, copy-pasteable commands)
6. Usage example
7. Project structure (brief)
8. Notes on limitations or future work, if any

Keep the tone direct and technical — no marketing fluff, no filler adjectives.
